e above section [Including Additional Header Files](#_mfcnotes_tn035_including)."},{"pos":[22090,22139],"content":"How Visual C++ Manages Set Includes Information**"},{"content":"As discussed above, the File menu Set Includes command lets you specify three types of information:","pos":[22146,22245]},{"content":"Symbol Header File","pos":[22255,22273]},{"content":"Read-Only Symbol Directives","pos":[22283,22310]},{"content":"Compile-Time Directives","pos":[22320,22343]},{"content":"The following describes how Visual C++ maintains this information in a .RC file.","pos":[22350,22430]},{"content":"You do not need this information to use Visual C++, but it may enhance your understanding so that you can more confidently use the Set Includes feature.","pos":[22431,22583]},{"content":"Each of the above three types of Set Includes information is stored in the .RC file in two forms: (1) as #include or other directives interpretable by the Resource Compiler, and (2) as special TEXTINCLUDE resources interpretable only by Visual C++.","pos":[22590,22838]},{"content":"The purpose of the TEXTINCLUDE resource is to safely store Set Include information in a form that is readily presentable in Visual C++'s <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Set Includes<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> dialog box.","pos":[22845,23010],"source":"The purpose of the TEXTINCLUDE resource is to safely store Set Include information in a form that is readily presentable in Visual C++'s **Set Includes** dialog box."},{"content":"TEXTINCLUDE is a <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>resource type<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> defined by Visual C++.","pos":[23011,23066],"source":" TEXTINCLUDE is a *resource type* defined by Visual C++."},{"content":"Visual C++ recognizes three specific TEXTINCLUDE resources that have the resource identification numbers 1, 2 and 3:","pos":[23067,23183]},{"content":"TEXTINCLUDE resource ID","pos":[23190,23213]},{"content":"Type of Set Includes information","pos":[23214,23246]},{"content":"1","pos":[23324,23325]},{"content"